Filters allows code to be run in specific stages before/after the code in specific pipelines.

Built-In filters - used for authorization, response caching, etc.
Custom Filters for cross-cutting features such as logging, exception handling, etc

Filters run inside the .net core action-invokation pipeline, also called fiter-pipeline.

Request -> Other middlewares -> Routing middlewares -> Action Selection -> MVC Action -> Action Selection -> Routing Middleware -> Other Middleware
